modules.description: Provides functions for parsing and validating command-line arguments, including option extraction and error handling. Operates on strings and lists, transforming raw input into structured data. Used to process user input in CLI tools, ensuring correct parameter interpretation.

Provides string interpolation by expanding expressions within format strings, using location and path information to generate valid OCaml code. Works with OCaml AST nodes, specifically expressions and locations, to inject evaluated values into string literals. Used to transform code like "hello %{name}" into "hello " ^ name during preprocessing.
